<serverless_attacks_guide>
<title>SERVERLESS SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Serverless functions (AWS Lambda, Azure Functions, Google Cloud Functions) have unique attack surfaces including cold start exploitation, event injection, environment variable leakage, function URL bypass, and execution role abuse. Focus on ephemeral nature, event-driven triggers, and IAM/role permissions.</critical>

<scope>
- Lambda/Cloud Function exploitation and code injection
- Cold start timing attacks and resource exhaustion
- Event injection attacks (SQS, SNS, S3, API Gateway, etc.)
- Environment variable leakage and secrets exposure
- Function URL and API Gateway bypass
- Execution role abuse and privilege escalation
- Layer poisoning and dependency confusion
- Function timeout and memory exhaustion
- Logging and monitoring evasion
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify serverless functions (Lambda, Azure Functions, Cloud Functions)
2. Map event sources and triggers (API, queues, storage, etc.)
3. Test event injection and payload manipulation
4. Enumerate environment variables and IAM roles
5. Probe for code injection and command execution
6. Test cold start and resource limit exploitation
7. Analyze function URL/API Gateway security
8. Attempt privilege escalation via execution role
</methodology>

